    colors = cycle(COLORS)

fig, ax = plt.subplots()

    # create a color iterator for each line
    color_iter = cycle(COLORS)
    for data in list_of_lists:
        # skip empty data sets
        if len(data) == 0:
            continue

        # shuffle y-values
        shuffled_data = data.copy()
        shuffle(shuffled_data)

        # plot line with shuffled y-values and sequential x-values
        x = range(1, len(data)+1)
        color = next(color_iter)
        ax.plot(x, shuffled_data, label=str(data), color=color)

    ax.set_xlabel("X-Axis")
    ax.set_ylabel("Y-Axis")
    ax.set_title("Shuffled Lines")
    ax.legend()
    plt.show()
    return fig, ax

fig = plt.figure(1)
    ax = fig.add_subplot(111)

    x = np.arange(1, list_of_lists[0][0]+1, 1)
    # shuffles the y values in each list in list_of_lists
    [shuffle(lst) for lst in list_of_lists]
    # zip() together x and each list in list_of_lists
    # cycle() makes sure the same colors are reused if there are more lists than colors
    [ax.plot(x, y, color=color) for y, color in zip(list_of_lists, cycle(COLORS))]
    return fig, ax
